{
  "stem": "24885.1",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "The original name home was Lipschitz.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Now it's Lipson.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You'll see him in some magazines.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I knew them from home, you know, and a lot of them.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this is short of what happened Poland.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We didn't have-- we lived in the same place.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't have no problems.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My parents dealt with Christians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It turned out later, I found out they were not Christians, they were what we called Volksdeutsche.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They were Germans who lived in the-- but they were still Polish.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS]",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then the war started in the end of '39, and things took a turn.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When Germans came in, from the day they came in, they were looking for Jews.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "First, for Jews with beards, and they shaved them off.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They made spectacles out of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Get them into a-- gather them in a place and made them kneel and so on while somebody-- they had-- while they shave their beards off and they had a picnic with it, and the beatings, and everything else.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I do have some pictures that I took up for magazines.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I might have been, but you run away.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You didn't want to see it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You brought the subject up, and I'll tell you something.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It took me three years, until 1944 when they marched us from-- I'm going ahead of myself-- from Radom to Auschwitz because they couldn't get trains anymore.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I had hoped that maybe I'll survive.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And one of them tried to run away and they caught him.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And of course, the many German volunteers who had volunteered to shoot him right away.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I said to my brother, I said, I better look around, I want to see what, what it is like when you shoot somebody.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 47,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I want to see it.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
